# Git Commit Approval Required

NEVER run `git commit`, `git push`, or any destructive git command without explicit user approval.

## Required workflow

1. Show the user what will be committed (`git status`, `git diff --stat`)
2. Propose the commit message
3. Wait for explicit confirmation ("oui", "go", "commit", etc.)
4. Only then run `git commit`

## Same rule applies to

- `git push`
- `git rebase`
- `git reset`
- `git merge`
